OL,3,GDumfries, Galloway, Lothian & Borders
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be a dry day with
OL,6,Fpatchy cloud and plenty of bright and
OL,7,Fsunny spells breaking through. Mostly
OL,8,Flight winds but breezy near the coast.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FA dry evening with late sunny
OL,11,Fspells leading to clear spells after
OL,12,Fsunset. Overnight remaining dry with
OL,13,Flong clear spells for most, but
OL,14,Fturning cloudier in the west of
OL,15,FDumfries.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSaturday:FSunny spells to start but
OL,18,Fsoon turning cloudy through the
OL,19,Fmorning. A cloudy afternoon with rain
OL,20,Fpushing eastwards, heavy at times in
OL,21,Fthe west but more patchy in east.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
